# Safety net: this git repo lives in the same folder as personal/client
# files on the Desktop. Nothing below should ever end up on the public
# GitHub Pages repo. This does NOT untrack files already committed —
# it only stops *new* files of these kinds from being added by accident.

# Client & personal documents
*.docx
*.xlsx
*.xlsm
*.csv
*.tsv
*.pdf
*.pptx
*.rtf

# Client data exports / backups (weight logs, restores, ergometric results, etc.)
*.json
*.log

# Photos / screenshots
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif

# App backup copies (timestamped snapshots made before edits)
*.backup
*.backup-*.html
*backup*.html
Dietologist.backup*
plan.backup*

# Known client-data / backup folders used by the app
Dietologist_App/backups/
Dietologist_App/data/
_CLOUD_MIGRATION_SAFE/

# Secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Installers / binaries
*.exe

# OS / editor cruft
desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# Internal dev/audit docs & deploy scripts — these sat tracked at repo root,
# which GitHub Pages serves publicly (feedyourhealth.github.io/<name>).
# Untracked 2026-07-04; listed by exact name (not a *.md wildcard) since
# README.md is meant to stay public.
ACCURACY_TEST_PLAN.md
CALCULATIONS_AUDIT.md
CODE_ANALYSIS_REPORT.md
FINAL_COMPLETION_SUMMARY.md
FULL_TEST_REPORT.md
HOW_TO_UPDATE.md
LIVE_TEST_SESSION.md
MEDITERRANEAN_AUDIT.md
POTENTIAL_BUGS_ANALYSIS.md
QUICK_TEST_CHECKLIST.txt
TEST_SUMMARY.md
SETUP_GITHUB.sh
update.bat
update.sh
